-- Bharat Petroleum Said to Buy Libya’s El Sharara From Total
-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 2013-03-13T12:20:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-13/bharat-petroleum-said-to-buy-libya-s-el-sharara-from-total-2-.html
Bharat Petroleum Corp. (BPCL) , India’s
second-largest state refiner, bought 1 million barrels of Libyan
El Sharara crude for loading in April from  Total SA (FP) , said three
traders who asked not to be identified because the information
is confidential.  The Indian refiner paid about $1.85 a barrel more than
Dated Brent for the crude cargo, two of the traders said.  Bharat Petroleum previously purchased about 1 million
barrels each of the Nigerian Akpo, Angolan Nemba and Algerian
Saharan Blend grades for loading in April, data compiled by
Bloomberg show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
